# {name}

{name} tool.

## Quick Start

```bash
{short_name} --help              # Show help
{short_name} "query"             # Default action
```

## Built-in Eco Commands

All tools share these framework commands (triple-dash prefix):

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `---setup` | Run tool setup/installation |
| `---test` | Run unit tests |
| `---dev <cmd>` | Developer commands (info, sanity-check) |
| `---audit code` | Code quality audit |
| `---config show` | Show configuration |
| `---rule` | Show AI rules |

## Testing

```bash
TOOL ---test {name}
```

## Interface

```python
from tool.{name}.interface.main import get_info
info = get_info()
```
